text: bright,  brilliant,  colorful,  perfumed flowers grow in the garden in my backyard,  cottony,  petaled flowers bloom from the seedlings i planted in late spring,  juicy watermelons,  trickling down my throat,  burst with the most fruity flavor in summer,  large,  rounded,  midnight black and lemon yellow bumble bees buzz from flower to flower,  collecting as much nectar from every plant they can find in the chocolaty brown and forest green lawns,  i sniff the many smells of the turkey sandwiches,  chicken salad,  coleslaw,  and the best watermelon in my tie-dyed picnic basket,  siting at the park having a great picnic with my family.  nature. . . best time to be in summer.
